Transport Canada is investigating an incident involving a seaplane making a dangerous takeoff underneath a bridge in Ottawa last weekend, which onlookers described as 'suicidal'.

Footage of the stunt has since emerged, showing the pilot slowly lifting along the Ottawa River on Saturday morning, with terrified witnesses believing the plane wouldn't clear the Macdonald-Cartier Bridge it was heading directly for.

As rowers on the water stop to watch and people can be heard screaming and yelling, the light aircraft sails through two pylons of the bridge - which connects Ottawa and Gatineau - and out the other side.

'Honestly, I thought he was suicidal,' Lana Burpee, preisdent of the Ottawa Rowing, told The National Post after witnessing the takeoff.

