'I thought he was going to try to smash into the side of the bridge, but fortunately the pilot was able to get through that ascent safely.'

Burpee added that the pilot had only been 'a heartbeat away it could have been the worst-case scenario'.

She described the stunt as 'crazy, reckless and endangering', especially since there were numerous small boats and rowers on the river at the time.

It is unusual to see seaplanes on the Ottawa River.

Investigations into the the takeoff continue to see whether the pilot could face penalties for the stunt.

Video, taken by Burpee's husband Peter, was uploaded to Youtube.

